Create a `src/logger.js` module that provides a simple logging utility. It should export a `log(level, message)` function supporting levels: 'info', 'warn', and 'error'. Each level should prefix the message with a label (e.g. [INFO], [WARN], [ERROR]) and output to the appropriate console method (console.log, console.warn, console.error). Update index.js to use the logger instead of console.log directly.